00:16:00.750 --> 00:16:01.950
Wallet, e.g.

00:16:01.950 --> 00:16:03.910
a HTTP post?

00:16:03.910 --> 00:16:06.530
I don't want to use any client
side code to provide my own

00:16:06.530 --> 00:16:08.640
web page and that does
all the charging.

00:16:11.220 --> 00:16:13.740
It seems to me that you're
looking for more of a payment

00:16:13.740 --> 00:16:16.550
gateway functionality, where you
can just pass over credit

00:16:16.550 --> 00:16:20.790
card information and then charge
that amount and capture

00:16:20.790 --> 00:16:23.490
the proceeds of the sale.

00:16:23.490 --> 00:16:27.470
Currently, Google Wallet
doesn't offer any

00:16:27.470 --> 00:16:29.780
