always need to complete on

00:16:34.760 --> 00:16:37.000
Google Wallet slash
Google Checkout.

00:16:37.000 --> 00:16:40.660
However, we do offer
a new flow.

00:16:40.660 --> 00:16:45.500
It's called Google Wallet
for Online Commerce.

00:16:45.500 --> 00:16:49.690
The difference is that it's like
a OAuth 2 style access to

00:16:49.690 --> 00:16:52.520
Google Payment Credentials.

00:16:52.520 --> 00:16:56.070
So what we'll do is we'll
actually pass you over, you as

00:16:56.070 --> 00:16:59.120
a merchant, a one time use
card that you can charge

00:16:59.120 --> 00:17:00.770
against your payment gateway.

00:17:00.770 --> 00:17:02.880
So that's something that's a
little bit different and maybe

00:17:02.880 --> 00:17:05.520
more useful to you.

00:17:05.520 --> 00:17:09.660
For just the payment gateway
aspect of it, you may be more

00:17:09.660 --> 00:17:14.849
interested in a solution such
as authorize.net or Chase

00:17:14.849 --> 00:17:21.610
Paymentech, that can perform
the API charge requests.

