00:17:41.210 --> 00:17:44.000
The question is, I have trouble
posting a digital

00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:45.340
subscription order.

00:17:45.340 --> 00:17:47.440
I get a purchased cancelled
failure code.

00:17:47.440 --> 00:17:49.850
How do I debug this?

00:17:49.850 --> 00:17:54.780
So purchase canceled indicates
that either the buyer

00:17:54.780 --> 00:17:57.690
cancelled the transaction,
or something went

00:17:57.690 --> 00:17:59.910
wrong with the order.

00:17:59.910 --> 00:18:05.040
Either the payment failed or
there was some time out, some

00:18:05.040 --> 00:18:08.510
expiration, and the order
is not valid anymore.

00:18:08.510 --> 00:18:12.026
So I would, first, have
a look at the JWT.

00:18:12.026 --> 00:18:14.890
You are correctly constructing
the JWT.

00:18:14.890 --> 00:18:18.980
Google is not rejecting it,
but check the issued and

00:18:18.980 --> 00:18:20.750
expiration times.

00:18:20.750 --> 00:18:23.610
Those may not be
valid anymore.

00:18:23.610 --> 00:18:27.890
And then Google thinks that
the order has expired.

00:18:27.890 --> 00:18:31.190
And it simply returns
the error code.

00:18:31.190 --> 00:18:35.620
Second, check your buyer
account, the sample buyer

00:18:35.620 --> 00:18:37.100
account you're using
for this purchase.

00:18:37.100 --> 00:18:40.740
Make sure the credit cards
look correctly.

00:18:40.740 --> 00:18:45.350
They are the test cards
that we're offering.

00:18:45.350 --> 00:18:47.630
And generally, that there's
nothing wrong

00:18:47.630 --> 00:18:49.640
with the buyer account.

00:18:49.640 --> 00:18:51.610
Try different credit cards--

00:18:51.610 --> 00:18:55.290
we have at least four that you
can try with-- and see if that

00:18:55.290 --> 00:18:56.770
fixes the problem.

00:18:56.770 --> 00:19:00.950
If none of this works, then I
would go and try one of our

00:19:00.950 --> 00:19:06.250
samples on the developer
sample code site

00:19:06.250 --> 00:19:08.750
and then work backwards.

00:19:08.750 --> 00:19:12.810
Do changes to that sample one
by one to match your changes

00:19:12.810 --> 00:19:14.060
and see if it breaks.

